the cpu
 note: i am onli show motorola & intel cpu us in mac and most ibm/pc 
clone machin. for exampl, sinc appl never us the motorola 68008 and 
68010 in the mac these chip ar not list. year onli appear with dead cpu 
and indic first to last year us as a cpu.
cach note:  both ibm and mac us cach extern to the cpu. these extern 
cach increas the speed of the cpu but ar not a part of it.  in most of 
the present mac there ar extern cach built-in while with ibm thei ar 
option {though machin ar gener sold with them instal}.  sinc 
there ar mani differ extern cach {cpu-mac and ibm; scsi, video, disk 
and static ram-mac}, each have a differ effect on cpu perform, and 
thei ar machin {32kb static ram cach in iici, iifx, and iivx}, seller 
{cach card instal in some iici} or expans {iici cach card go up to 
128kb} depend, i have decid to leav them out of the list.
