expans
both mac & ibm
scsi: onli extern devic expans interfac common to both mac and ibm.
 allow the us of ani devic: hard drive, printer, scanner, nubu card 
 expans {mac plu onli}, some monitor, and cd-rom.  
 main problem:  there ar a lot of extern devic which ar intern 
 termin which caus problem for more then two devis off the scsi port 
 {a scsi chain is suppos to be termin onli at the begin and at the 
 end.  ani other set up caus problem for either mac or ibm}. 
scsi-1:  7 devic per scsi control.  8-bit asynchron {~1.5mb/s av}
 and synchron {5mb/s max} transfer.  differ is due to scsi-1 softwar
 driver.  "fast scsi-1" is a misnam for 8-bit scsi-2 in scsi-1 mode
 {see scsi-2 for detail}.
scsi-2: 10 devic per scsi control in scsi-2 mode.  scsi-2 is fulli
 scsi-1 compliant and 8-bit scsi-2 tend to be implement as a veri fast
 scsi-1 sinc it doe not requir the differ control interfac in  
 hardwar and softwar that 16 and 32-bit scsi-2 do.  transfer speed ar
 4-6mb/s with 10mb/s burst {8-bit}, 8-12mb/s with 20mb/s burst {16-bit}, and
 15-20mb/s with 40mb/s burst {32-bit/wide and fast}.  sinc 8-bit scsi-2 can
 us scsi-1 softwar driver and hardwar at 8-bit scsi-2 speed and as such
 is limit to 7 devic sometim it is mistakenli call "fast scsi-1". 
 16-bit fast scsi-2 requir a scsi-2 softwar driver and scsi-2 electron
 but can still us the scsi-1 port.  wide 16-bit and 32-bit scsi-2 requir a
 differ scsi port, electron, and softwar driver from scsi-1 {which
 make them more expens than other scsi interfac}.
mac scsi: asynchron scsi-1 built-in standard sinc the plu.  even though 
 appl develop some specif for scsi control, the os scsi manag
 need to be rewritten to take full advantag of the featur of both scsi
 interfac.  as a result present scsi-2 mac us 8-bit scsi-2 as a fast 
 asynchron scsi-1.  present quadra ar the onli mac with a scsi-2
 control chip built-in (digit review, oct 21, 1991 v8 n33 p8(1)) 
 though thei lack some other part of the hardwar, like the wide scsi-2 port 
 interfac.  sinc other mac requir a nubu card to us scsi-2, older nubu 
 mac had a bottleneck due to the speed of the nubu and cpu.  rumor-some
 cyclon mac {june} will come with a wide & fast scsi-2 port standard 
 and have a rewritten os scsi manag.
ibm scsi:  scsi-1 is not too wide spread yet, gener not bundl with 
 system, except as add-on {eisa and vesa local bu adapt aval}.
 like the mac, 8-bit scsi-2 is us as a veri fast scsi-1 by most control
 out there.  unlik the mac, ibm ha no exact scsi control specif
 which result in ad incompat for scsi.

mac
memori expans: with a few except the mac ha us non-pariti 30-pin 
 8-bit simm memori expans sinc the plu.  while 32-pin 9-bit pariti simm
 could be us in these mac, onli special iici could make us of the pariti 
 featur {by convens both simm type ar call 32-pin simm}.  the iifx 
 us 64-pin pariti simm.  the lc iii, c610/650 and q800 all us a new 
 72-pin simm that is access by 32-bit at a time and is us in ibm.
 the mac doe a complet memori check at startup by write/read everi
 memori locat; if someth is serious wrong with a simm the mac will
 not boot and give a sound chord indic what the problem is.
 sinc mac made befor feb 15, 1993 manag memori bace on data path, simm 
 had to be instal in pair {16-bit} or in set of 4 {32-bit}.  the centri 
 650 and quadra 800 elimin thi with a new memori manag setup that 
 allow memori to be upgrad on simm at a time.  if the simm ar the same 
 size ar us then the memori is 'interleav' across the two simm result 
 in a 10-15% perform boost on ram access (macworld apr 93: 108-109).
printer, adb, and modem: built-in interfac standard.
monitor interfac and sound input: built-in on most present mac. 
pd: avail in se & all present non-powerbook mac. 16-bit {se, 
 portabl, lc, lc ii, classic line} and 32-bit.  oper at cpu's mhz.  
 maximum through put: data path in byte*cpu's mhz {q700/900 & c650: 
 4 * 25mhz = 100mb/s; q800 & q950: 4 * 33mhz = 132mb/s}. standard with
 the lc and 040 bu design.  with an adapt on nubu card can be us in 
 iisi and c610.  problem: some card have time depend which slow 
 through put down.
nubu mac ii: 32-bit, 10 mhz bu clock, 1-to-1 transact/bu cycl ratio,
 and contigu, hand-shake transact at ~10-20mb/s; theoret peak:
 40mb/s.  built-in on all modular mac except the lc seri, c610, and 
 performa 400.  the se/30 could be adapt to us thi and there wa even a 
 mac plu scsi nubu.  support everi possibl expans from cpu to ethernet 
 to dma.
nubu 90: nubu mac ii back compat. 20mhz bu clock, avg throughput:
 ~30mb/s; burst mode: 80mb/s.  futur card design will be 7" instead of the 
 old 12".
quickr:  a peer-to-peer bu us in parallel with nubu 90.  appl's 
 vlbu - "architectur is ident to that of vlbu" (byte 10/92:128).
 burst mode: 350mb/s (byte 10/92:128). in develop.
cpu expans: handl either through the pd or the nubu.  unlik pd,  
 nubu cpu card {exampl-radiu rocket} allow us of multipl processor at 
 the same time.  thi is like have two or more mac in the same box abl to 
 dual task or joinli process depend on the card or softwar involv {each 
 nubu card need it own memori but most nubu card of thi type come with 
 8mb ram simm on the card standard}.

