os number crunch (mel park)
mac
 arithmet is done in a consist numer environ {sane or standard 
appl numer environ}. float point number ar 96 bit long when an 
fpu is present and 80 bit otherwis. except, such as divid by zero or 
take the squar root of a neg number, do not caus an abort but ar 
handl in a logic consist manner. 1/0 produc the intern 
represent for infin (inf).  1/(1/0) produc zero. the abov treatment 
of 1/(1/0) occur in an fpu-equip machin even when sane is bypass and 
the fpu program directli.

ibm
 float point number ar 80-bit with a hardwar fpu, 64-bit when 
emul.  the wai thei ar handl is depend on the code of whatev 
compil or assembl wa us for a program. on older do complil 
except could caus program abort; 1/0 and 1/(1/0) would abort to the do 
prompt at the point where thei occur.  most present compil handl thi 
better.  result: there is littl consist handl of number between do, 
window and os/2 program nor between program for just on os.

network [includ print]
wysiwyg print can be a problem with either mac of ibm machin especi 
if on send truetyp font to a older style postscript printer.
mac
hardwar: built-in localtalk network port and a built-in printer port.  
localtalk ha moder speed (230.4 kb/s) requir special connector for 
each machin ($15 and up) and can be run off of either the printer port {to 
includ veri old mac} or the network port {standard todai}.  built-in 
ethernet is becom common but mani older mac requir a pd or nubu card at 
about $150-$300 for each machin.  these card provid three connector and 
transceiv {thick, thin, and 10baset} for ethernet.
the macintosh quadra famili and some centri model includ ethernet 
interfac on motherboard, with transceiv avail. tokenr ha been a 
network option sinc 1989.
softwar: appletalk {the suit of protocol} standard with mac os, which can 
us varieti of media type.  appleshar client softwar includ with the os 
as well and can connect to file server such as novel netwar, 3com 3+open, 
banyan vine, dec pathwork, appl's appleshar server, system 7 file share 
machin, and afp server run on varieti of unix host.  mactcp allow 
typic tcp/ip commun (telnet, ftp, nf, rlogin).  a later version 
will have unix x/open transport interfac (xti) built-in by the end of 1993 
(macweek 04/12/93).  third-parti softwar to connect to nf server.  dec 
pathwork provid decnet support.  peer-to-peer file share softwar 
built-in to system 7.1 (see os section).  full server softwar is extra. 
print requir connect of the printer and the printer be select in 
the chooser.  chang printer is by select a differ name in the 
chooser.  the same is true of connect to server.
print bug:  monaco truetyp font is differ then the screen bitmap font.
 {quickdraw qx is supposs to fix thi and similar problem.}

ibm  
hardwar: localtalk [not wide us], ethernet,  and tokenr.
softwar: novel netwar, banyan vine, decnet, window/work group, appletalk 
protocol, and appleshar {subset of appletalk}.
each of the ms-do network scheme ar, in gener, total incompat 
with the other. onc you have chosen on, you ar pretti much lock-in to 
that product line from then on.  window/work group is a littl more 
forgiv and remov some of thi problem.  novel netwar is the biggest, 
{~80 percent of the corpor market.} and in gener is more power and 
offer better control/manag/secur than appleshar, but it's also more 
complex to set up and manag.  thi will chang due to the us of the mac 
finder and file manag system by novel. (pc week 12/14/92 & 12/28/92;  
infoworld dec 14/92; macweek 3/22/93)
